song_name: Never Seen The Light Of Day

version_description: Transcribed from the official music video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4cHb8AJDR5Y ... Note about chords: you can substitute Cmaj7 for C and Am7 for Am, according to what sounds better to you. Sometimes the ambient notes in the recording combine with the guitar to produce these more colorful chords.
A simple acoustic version with very basic chords and strumming.

Into The Fire Original Version Acoustic. You could see the strumming in the video. I wrote down exactly the chords the guitar player was playing. Didn't change anything, it's all original. Enjoy And Keep Rockin'.

Acoustic version of this song. These chords are exactly what Ben Bruce is playing on an acoustic session at KBPI - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t35Fh9dUNfM. I added few chords, because they make the song sound even better, they are marked with stars, but you can just keep it simple and play it without them.

This version is a good starting place for novice players who tune their guitars in standard tuning or those with lower vocal ranges. Use a capo on 4 to match the key of the official acoustic release of this song. https://youtu.be/x8uljvyUDuw.
A reasonably simple acoustic version of the song.

This version are original chords and tuning they actually use to the song Vultures by Asking Alexandria. You can check them on their acoustic session at KBPI - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oIUkKTbckAQ.
